args: It's just you, me, and the beach at last.\nI couldn't ask for anything better. Ahhh...
I'm glad you're happy, Alex. But, er...\nWhy do you have that bow with you?
Oh, this? Think of it as...extra security.
(A must, considering what she told me.)
Alex, I do have one warning about this\nparticular villa...
Fiends miiiiight attack from the ocean\nwhile you're on the private beach.\nSo do be careful.
You know, fiends? Evil and full of juicy\nbits? The place where the villa is located\ntends to have an outbreak every few years.
And once they show up, it means trouble...\nbut hey, it doesn't happen all that much,\nso I'm sure it's fine! Probably.
(Unbelievable. We finally got away from\npeople, only to possibly have FIENDS\ndescend upon us?)
(I brought a weapon just in case, but I do\nhope I don't end up having to use it.)
(Fortunately, Elisanne has her back turned\nto them and hasn't noticed yet—meaning\nI can do THIS!)
Elisanne! Look, up in the sky!\nWhat the hell is that?!
(There we go. If Elisanne had noticed\nthe fiends, she would've started to think\nvacationing was out of the question.)
Er... I'm not seeing anything, Alex.
Sorry. Must've been my eyes playing\ntricks on me.
?! Elisanne, get down!\nSomething's flying this way!
It DID feel like something whooshed over\nmy head there...
Although I have to say, it sounded more\nlike whatever it was came from your\ndirection than somewhere else.
Oh, um, yeah... That's because it was\ncoming from behind me, aiming for you.
Wow. You've got fantastic senses if you\npicked up on something in your blind spot\nlike that.
Totally. I'm always on the lookout\nfor these sorts of things.
Again?! Elisanne, um... Close your eyes!\nI've got a bad feeling the wind is going to\nkick sand into them!
I knew something weird was going on.\nHonestly, you are an AWFUL liar, Alex.
Urgh... I'm sorry. I thought that if you\nrealized there were fiends afoot, you'd\npull the plug on our vacation.
I see. It means a lot that you'd put so\nmuch effort into making me happy...
...but I really wish you'd stop pushing\nyourself so hard to do everything alone.
I barely broke a sweat, though.
That's not what I mean, Alex.
Fiends again?! We'll talk after we\nmop them up!
Right. I've had enough interruptions for\none day.
Hrk... There're too many of them!
This is bad. Some of them got away, and\nthey're headed for a beach with lots of\npeople on it!
It's total chaos. We run the risk of hurting\nbystanders if we charge in headfirst.
First, we need to evacuate the area.\nHeeey! Run for the square over that way!
It's no good. They're so panicked,\nthey're not hearing me!
It is! Surely she'll be able to help\nus like she did back at the contest!
Why are they focused on ME?!
No, this is perfect. You can use this\nopportunity to make them listen to you!
(This'll be just like when I brought people\ninto the cafe. Just be amiable like then,\nand...)
You have nothing to fear, friends!\nI promise you, I will defeat these fiends.
But to do that, I need you all to evacuate to\nthe square in a calm and orderly fashion!
Whatever you say, Alex!\nWe trust you!
Excellent. Now we can fight without worry.\nHaaah!
Back-to-back formation, Elisanne.\nLet's clean this mess up once and for all.
And that looks like all of them.
Our beach is saved thanks to you!
Let's sing our summertime savior's\npraises as we toss her into the air!
Hold on, now! I'd really rather you didn't—
Gah! I've heard the phrase ＂the crowd\ngoes wild,＂ but this is ridiculous.
Come out, Alex! Let us thank you!
The whole villa's surrounded by rabid\nAlex fans. This sure is, uh, a thing.
She'll be mobbed in a flash if she\nso much as steps a toe outside.
With the throngs this thick, the people\nare liable to flood onto the private beach\nany second.
I can't believe this...\nThis villa was my last ray of hope.
